deleverageAccount(address,address,addres.notice: If an account is below the minimum collateral ratio, this method wil deleverage (liquidate) that account. `depositAmountExternal` in the borrow currency will be transferred from the liquidator and used to offset the account's debt position. The liquidator will receive either vaultShares or cash depending on the vault's configuration.

params.account: the address that will exit the vault
params.depositAmountExternal: amount of asset cash to deposit
params.liquidator: the address that will receive profits from liquidation
params.redeemData: calldata sent to the vault when redeeming liquidator profits

returns.profitFromLiquidation: amount of vaultShares or cash received from liquidation

enterVault(address,address,uint256,uint2.notice: Borrows a specified amount of fCash in the vault's borrow currency and deposits it all plus the depositAmountExternal into the vault to mint strategy tokens.

params.account: the address that will enter the vault
params.depositAmountExternal: some amount of additional collateral in the borrowed currency to be transferred to vault
params.maxBorrowRate: maximum interest rate to borrow at
params.useUnderlying: true if the account will transfer underlying tokens
params.vaultData: additional data to pass to the vault contract

exitVault(address,address,uint256,uint25.notice: Prior to maturity, allows an account to withdraw their position from the vault. Will redeem some number of vault shares to the borrow currency and close the borrow position by lending `fCashToLend`. Any shortfall in cash from lending will be transferred from the account, any excess profits will be transferred to the account. Post maturity, will net off the account's debt against vault cash balances and redeem all remaining strategy tokens back to the borrowed currency and transfer the profits to the account.

params.account: the address that will exit the vault
params.exitVaultData: passed to the vault during exit
params.minLendRate: the minimum rate to lend at
params.useUnderlying: if vault shares should be redeemed to underlying
params.vaultSharesToRedeem: amount of vault tokens to exit, only relevant when exiting pre-maturity

rollVaultPosition(address,address,uint25.notice: Re-enters the vault at a longer dated maturity. The account's existing borrow position will be closed and a new borrow position at the specified maturity will be opened. All strategy token holdings will be rolled forward.

params.account: the address that will reenter the vault
params.fCashToBorrow: amount of fCash to borrow in the next maturity
params.opts: struct with slippage limits and data to send to vault
